%N A397944 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} H(k)*H(k,2)/(2*k+1)^2, where H(k) = A001008(k)/A002805(k) is the k-th harmonic number, and H(k,2) = A007406(k)/A007407(k) is the k-th generalized harmonic number of order 2.
%H A397944 Cornel Ioan Vălean, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-21262-8">More (Almost) Impossible Integrals, Sums, and Series</a>, Springer Cham, 2023. See section 4.34, p. 433-434, eq. (4.128), section 5.34, p. 464, section 6.33, pp. 671-675.
